  "texts": [
    "This test is repeated with many interrogators, and if they are unable to reliably tell the human player apart from the machine, then Turing argues that the machine is able to think.",
    "Turing proposed several variations on the test (Turing, 2004; Turing et al., 2004), which go beyond the scope of this paper.",
    "The interested reader might consult Copeland and Proudfoot (2009) for an extended discussion.",
    "The Turing Test was designed to test a machine's ability to think.",
    "However, as time has passed, the terms \"Turing Test\" and \"imitation game\" have often been used interchangeably in various research contexts."
  ],
